articles.title: Frene Ginwala's handling of arms deal inquiry the one blemish on an otherwise unmatched record - News24
articles.description: Former National Assembly speaker Frene Ginwala has been remembered as an "exemplary leader" who contributed immensely to the struggle for democracy in South Africa. Ginwala died at the age of 90 on Thursday after suffering a stroke two weeks ago.
